.TH "evm_inode_post_removexattr" 9 "evm_inode_post_removexattr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
evm_inode_post_removexattr \- update 'security.evm' after removing the xattr
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" evm_inode_post_removexattr
.BI "(struct dentry *dentry "  ","
.BI "const char *xattr_name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dentry" 12
pointer to the affected dentry
.IP "xattr_name" 12
pointer to the affected extended attribute name
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Update the HMAC stored in 'security.evm' to reflect removal of the xattr.

No need to take the i_mutex lock here, as this function is called from
\fBvfs_removexattr\fP which takes the i_mutex.
